meetings.title: Secure Coding Practices - Lunch & Learn 🥪👩🏻‍🏫👨🏽‍🏫
meetings.description:
Join us here:https://biorender.zoom.us/j/81944299935

Hi Team, 

We're excited to host Brandon Caldwell for a talk on secure coding practices across a company’s lifecycle. He’ll share insights from his experience scaling security programs in both small and large organizations.

About the Speaker

Brandon has over 15 years of experience in security, including 9 years at Microsoft, 5 years as Head of AppSec at Unity—where he scaled the function pre-IPO from ~500 to ~4,000 employees—and is currently a Manager at Amazon/AWS. He has built and matured secure software development practices (SSDLCs) at every stage of company growth.

Looking forward seeing you all for some food for thought and facts and snacks. It's going to be a knowledge feast!  🥪🧠

meetings.title: BioRender 2025 Summer Event
meetings.description:
☀️ Summer Synergy – BioRender Offsite ☀️

Get ready for an exciting week of collaborating, hacking, and connecting as we bring the entire BioRender team together in Toronto!

Location: 49 Spadina Ave., Unit 200, ON, Toronto, M5V 2J1 

*Please make your way to the office where we'll have breakfast and drinks at 9:00 am EST*    

What to bring: 

🍵 Reusable beverage cup/mug 
📒 Notebook & pen 
💻 Laptop & charger 
🎧 Headphones 

Find more information on our Summer Synergy 2025 doc 

See information on the event and booking travel https://biorender.slack.com/archives/C08QA27J6JU/p1745607951907349

meetings.title: Breakfast // Swag Pick-Up // 9:30 AM Welcome & Kick Off!
meetings.description:
🎉 Time to Kick Off Summer Synergy 2025! ☀️

Join us in person at the office (49 Spadina Ave) to kick things off with some tasty breakfast treats to start your day right. 🥐☕️ 

8:30 - 9:30 AM - Breakfast & Swag Pick Up
  • Breakfast served in North All Hands & South Kitchen
  • Pick up your name tags and swag!
    • For those who are unable to make it Tues morning, please see an organizer team member (has a reflective yellow armband) to get your swag when you arrive!

9:30 - 10 AM - Welcome & Kick Off
  • Zoom Link to join remotely - Zoom Link
  • Expect a quick overview of what’s ahead, a few words from leadership, and let's get energized for the week!
  • First a spot in North All Hands (main stage) & South Kitchen (TV broadcast) to watch
  • Haven't joined a Hackathon team yet - Last chance!

Information
  • Follow #summer-synergy-2025 in Slack for announcements/most up to date information
  • See our Summer Synergy overview doc for more info

meetings.title: Day 1: Summer Synergy Hackathon
meetings.description:
☀️ Summer Synergy – BioRender Offsite ☀️

Location: 49 Spadina Ave., Unit 200, ON, Toronto, M5V 2J1 

What to bring: 

🍵 Reusable beverage cup/mug 
📒 Notebook & pen 
💻 Laptop & charger 
🎧 Headphones 

Kickoff & Hack Time
We’ll start the day with a brief kickoff session to set the stage, and then you’ll break out into your teams to begin hacking. Get ready to collaborate, create, and bring your ideas to life!

Breaks & Activities:
🍽 Lunch: Served from 12:00 PM – 1:00 PM.
🧋 Boba & Guest Speaker: Join us from 3:00 PM – 4:00 PM for a special session with an external speaker, plus enjoy a refreshing boba break while you listen.

meetings.title: Day 3: Summer Synergy All Hands Sessions
meetings.description:
It’s time for our Summer Synergy All-Hands! This session will be broadcast on Zoom and recorded. 

BioRender Journey and Internal Panels: 
Link to join remotely - Link

We’ve got an exciting agenda lined up — join us as we share key updates, team highlights, and a few surprises along the way.

🌟 Special Guest Speaker:
Link to join remotely - Link

We’ll be joined by an external speaker from 1:00 – 1:30 PM for an inspiring session you won’t want to miss.

🖥️ Hackathon Finalist Presentations Awards:
Link to join remotely - Link

Hackathon finalists will be chosen Wednesday night after demo video submissions are completed. Finalists will then get to present their demos LIVE

🏆 Award Ceremony:

We’ll wrap things up by celebrating your incredible work the past year and during the hackathon with our Values and Hckathon award ceremony — get ready to cheer!

Make sure you stick around till the end as we'll cap things off with our annual company-wide team photo! 📷

recurring_meetings.title: Secure Coding Practices - Lunch & Learn 🥪👩🏻‍🏫👨🏽‍🏫
recurring_meetings.description:
Join us here:https://biorender.zoom.us/j/81944299935

Hi Team, 

We're excited to host Brandon Caldwell for a talk on secure coding practices across a company’s lifecycle. He’ll share insights from his experience scaling security programs in both small and large organizations.

About the Speaker

Brandon has over 15 years of experience in security, including 9 years at Microsoft, 5 years as Head of AppSec at Unity—where he scaled the function pre-IPO from ~500 to ~4,000 employees—and is currently a Manager at Amazon/AWS. He has built and matured secure software development practices (SSDLCs) at every stage of company growth.

Looking forward seeing you all for some food for thought and facts and snacks. It's going to be a knowledge feast!  🥪🧠

☀️ Summer Synergy – BioRender Offsite ☀️

Get ready for an exciting week of collaborating, hacking, and connecting as we bring the entire BioRender team together in Toronto!

Location: 49 Spadina Ave., Unit 200, ON, Toronto, M5V 2J1 

*Please make your way to the office where we'll have breakfast and drinks at 9:00 am EST*    

What to bring: 

🍵 Reusable beverage cup/mug 
📒 Notebook & pen 
💻 Laptop & charger 
🎧 Headphones

  • Breakfast served in North All Hands & South Kitchen

9:30 - 10 AM - Welcome & Kick Off

Information

Hi all,

Currently doing a review of Finance team software here with a discussion of gaps in our software ecosystem today.  To provide Kiran and David more context, we would like to dig in deeper into:

1) Lack of integration between Salesforce CRM and NetSuite
2) Lack of automation around Soft Serve
3) Manual nature of sales tax reconciliations causing inability to expand to additional countries due to bandwidth constraints
4) Issues around initial setup of NetSuite
